[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1681},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers\u002F":1656,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers\u002F":1665},"\u002Fother\u002F20260417\u002F830271645\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1638,"date":1639,"description":1640,"extension":1641,"lang":1642,"meta":1643,"navigation":410,"path":1644,"readingMinutes":1645,"seo":1646,"standalone":1647,"stem":1648,"tags":1649,"tldr":1653,"updated":1639,"url":1654,"__hash__":1655},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fcache-firebase-storage-images-with-cloudflare-workers.md","Cache Firebase Storage Images with Cloudflare Workers — Completely Free Bandwidth Savings","6082403517",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1611},"minimark",[11,18,23,26,38,42,45,48,78,85,89,92,150,153,156,165,170,177,181,188,195,204,207,211,214,218,221,258,265,269,311,889,904,911,915,918,938,948,952,979,983,986,989,1033,1040,1043,1047,1050,1059,1062,1066,1069,1072,1081,1084,1093,1096,1119,1126,1316,1329,1339,1342,1353,1368,1384,1388,1391,1400,1407,1415,1418,1422,1425,1428,1466,1472,1476,1485,1489,1498,1502,1507,1527,1532,1541,1546,1555,1562,1566,1569,1572,1604,1607],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":6,"src":17},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Ffirebase-to-cloudflare-workers\u002FGemini_Generated_Image_tlv3s5tlv3s5tlv3_2816x1536_1280x698.png",[19,20,22],"h2",{"id":21},"intro","Intro",[12,24,25],{},"If you're using Firebase Storage to host blog images like I was, you've probably noticed bandwidth costs creeping up. Every time someone visits an article, the images load straight from Firebase Storage, and all of that bandwidth lands on your Firebase bill. The more articles and readers you have, the worse the bandwidth bill gets.",[12,27,28,29,33,34,37],{},"Is there a way to put a cache layer in front so images don't get fetched from Firebase Storage every time? Yes — and ",[30,31,32],"strong",{},"completely free",". This post walks through how to use ",[30,35,36],{},"Cloudflare Workers"," with a custom subdomain to cache Firebase Storage images, letting Cloudflare's global CDN absorb most of the traffic.",[19,39,41],{"id":40},"how-does-this-work","How does this work?",[12,43,44],{},"Before getting into the implementation, let's cover the principle. Otherwise you won't know why it works.",[12,46,47],{},"In short, we're going to put Cloudflare in front of Firebase Storage as a \"middleman\" that caches the images:",[49,50,55],"pre",{"className":51,"code":52,"language":53,"meta":54,"style":54},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","User → images.yourdomain.com → Cloudflare CDN (cache layer) → Firebase Storage\n                                      ↑\n                              If cached, return directly — never touch Firebase\n","txt","",[56,57,58,66,72],"code",{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,60,63],"span",{"class":61,"line":62},"line",1,[59,64,65],{},"User → images.yourdomain.com → Cloudflare CDN (cache layer) → Firebase Storage\n",[59,67,69],{"class":61,"line":68},2,[59,70,71],{},"                                      ↑\n",[59,73,75],{"class":61,"line":74},3,[59,76,77],{},"                              If cached, return directly — never touch Firebase\n",[12,79,80,81,84],{},"The first time someone requests an image, Cloudflare fetches it from Firebase Storage and stashes a copy at the edge. Every subsequent request goes straight from the edge — ",[30,82,83],{},"Firebase doesn't get hit",", which means no bandwidth charge on the Firebase side.",[19,86,88],{"id":87},"is-this-really-free","Is this really free?",[12,90,91],{},"Before we go any further, let me cover the cost — that's probably what most people care about anyway:",[93,94,95,108],"table",{},[96,97,98],"thead",{},[99,100,101,105],"tr",{},[102,103,104],"th",{},"Item",[102,106,107],{},"Cost",[109,110,111,120,127,134,142],"tbody",{},[99,112,113,117],{},[114,115,116],"td",{},"Cloudflare account",[114,118,119],{},"Free",[99,121,122,125],{},[114,123,124],{},"Cloudflare DNS hosting",[114,126,119],{},[99,128,129,131],{},[114,130,36],{},[114,132,133],{},"Free (100,000 requests\u002Fday, no credit card)",[99,135,136,139],{},[114,137,138],{},"Cloudflare CDN cached traffic",[114,140,141],{},"Free (no bandwidth cap)",[99,143,144,147],{},[114,145,146],{},"Custom domain for Worker",[114,148,149],{},"Supported on the free plan",[12,151,152],{},"All of it free. Cloudflare is one of the few CDNs that doesn't bill on bandwidth, and people have run 5–9 TB\u002Fmonth on the free plan without trouble.",[12,154,155],{},"And once a request hits cache, it doesn't go through the Worker at all — so it doesn't consume your daily 100k Worker invocation quota either. For blog images, this is more than enough.",[157,158,159],"blockquote",{},[12,160,161,164],{},[30,162,163],{},"Note","\nThe one requirement is that you own a domain and host its DNS with Cloudflare (which is also free).",[166,167,169],"h3",{"id":168},"watch-out-for-the-paid-traps","Watch out for the paid traps",[12,171,172,173,176],{},"The Workers free plan doesn't require a credit card, but the dashboard has features (Durable Objects, Workers AI, etc.) that might nudge you toward the $5\u002Fmonth paid plan. ",[30,174,175],{},"Don't click any \"upgrade\" button"," — we only need basic Worker functionality, none of those advanced features.",[19,178,180],{"id":179},"why-a-subdomain","Why a subdomain?",[12,182,183,184,187],{},"You might be thinking: \"why not just use ",[56,185,186],{},"yourdomain.com\u002Fimages\u002F...","?\"",[12,189,190,191,194],{},"Simple — if your main domain is already running a blog or another project, the paths can collide easily. A subdomain (like ",[56,192,193],{},"images.yourdomain.com",") is fully isolated and won't interfere with anything on the main site. And the final image URL ends up looking like:",[49,196,198],{"className":51,"code":197,"language":53,"meta":54,"style":54},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.yourdomain.com\u002Fblog2\u002Fai\u002Fmy-post\u002Fscreenshot.png\n",[56,199,200],{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,201,202],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,203,197],{},[12,205,206],{},"Way cleaner than the long Firebase Storage URL.",[19,208,210],{"id":209},"lets-build-it","Let's build it",[12,212,213],{},"Now that we've covered the principle and cost, on to the implementation.",[166,215,217],{"id":216},"step-1-host-your-domain-dns-on-cloudflare","Step 1: Host your domain DNS on Cloudflare",[12,219,220],{},"If your domain isn't on Cloudflare yet:",[222,223,224,236,243,249,252,255],"ol",{},[225,226,227,228,235],"li",{},"Sign up for a ",[229,230,234],"a",{"href":231,"rel":232},"https:\u002F\u002Fdash.cloudflare.com\u002Fsign-up",[233],"nofollow","Cloudflare"," account (free).",[225,237,238,239,242],{},"Click ",[30,240,241],{},"Add a site"," → enter your domain.",[225,244,245,246,248],{},"Pick the ",[30,247,119],{}," plan.",[225,250,251],{},"Cloudflare gives you two nameservers.",[225,253,254],{},"At your domain registrar, change nameservers to the ones Cloudflare gave you.",[225,256,257],{},"Back in Cloudflare, click confirm, wait for DNS to propagate (usually minutes to hours).",[157,259,260],{},[12,261,262,264],{},[30,263,163],{},"\nIf your domain's already on Cloudflare, skip to Step 2.",[166,266,268],{"id":267},"step-2-create-a-cloudflare-worker","Step 2: Create a Cloudflare Worker",[222,270,271,278,287,293,299,308],{},[225,272,273,274,277],{},"Cloudflare dashboard → left sidebar → ",[30,275,276],{},"Workers & Pages",".",[225,279,238,280,283,284,277],{},[30,281,282],{},"Create"," → ",[30,285,286],{},"Create Worker",[225,288,289,290,277],{},"Pick ",[30,291,292],{},"\"Start from Hello World!\"",[225,294,295,296,277],{},"Give it a name, e.g. ",[56,297,298],{},"image-proxy",[225,300,238,301,304,305,277],{},[30,302,303],{},"Deploy"," to create it, then ",[30,306,307],{},"Edit code",[225,309,310],{},"Delete the default code and paste this:",[49,312,316],{"className":313,"code":314,"language":315,"meta":54,"style":54},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","export default {\n  async fetch(request) {\n    \u002F\u002F Restrict allowed origins\n    const allowedOrigins = [\n      'https:\u002F\u002Fyourdomain.com',\n      'https:\u002F\u002Fwww.yourdomain.com',\n      'http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost', \u002F\u002F for local dev\n    ];\n\n    const referer = request.headers.get('Referer') || '';\n    const origin = request.headers.get('Origin') || '';\n\n    const isAllowed =\n      (!referer && !origin) || \u002F\u002F allow direct browser address-bar access\n      allowedOrigins.some((o) => referer.startsWith(o) || origin.startsWith(o));\n\n    if (!isAllowed) {\n      return new Response('Forbidden', { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    \u002F\u002F Build the Firebase Storage URL from the path\n    const url = new URL(request.url);\n    const path = encodeURIComponent(url.pathname.slice(1));\n    const firebaseUrl = `https:\u002F\u002Ffirebasestorage.googleapis.com\u002Fv0\u002Fb\u002FYOUR_PROJECT.appspot.com\u002Fo\u002F${path}?alt=media`;\n\n    const response = await fetch(firebaseUrl);\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      return new Response('Not Found', { status: 404 });\n    }\n\n    \u002F\u002F Set cache headers\n    const headers = new Headers(response.headers);\n    headers.set('Cache-Control', 'public, max-age=31536000, immutable');\n    headers.set('CDN-Cache-Control', 'max-age=31536000');\n    headers.set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n\n    return new Response(response.body, {\n      status: response.status,\n      headers,\n    });\n  },\n};\n","js",[56,317,318,331,347,353,369,379,387,399,405,412,446,473,478,489,515,554,559,573,599,605,610,616,634,661,682,687,705,710,722,743,748,753,759,777,799,818,837,842,855,861,867,873,881],{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,319,320,324,327],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,321,323],{"class":322},"sWyjQ","export",[59,325,326],{"class":322}," default",[59,328,330],{"class":329},"s_sBn"," {\n",[59,332,333,336,340,343],{"class":61,"line":68},[59,334,335],{"class":322},"  async",[59,337,339],{"class":338},"sj_SG"," fetch",[59,341,342],{"class":329},"(request) ",[59,344,346],{"class":345},"sMAXC","{\n",[59,348,349],{"class":61,"line":74},[59,350,352],{"class":351},"sQrFR","    \u002F\u002F Restrict allowed origins\n",[59,354,356,359,363,366],{"class":61,"line":355},4,[59,357,358],{"class":322},"    const",[59,360,362],{"class":361},"sCcAr"," allowedOrigins",[59,364,365],{"class":322}," =",[59,367,368],{"class":345}," [\n",[59,370,372,376],{"class":61,"line":371},5,[59,373,375],{"class":374},"sTRMh","      'https:\u002F\u002Fyourdomain.com'",[59,377,378],{"class":345},",\n",[59,380,382,385],{"class":61,"line":381},6,[59,383,384],{"class":374},"      'https:\u002F\u002Fwww.yourdomain.com'",[59,386,378],{"class":345},[59,388,390,393,396],{"class":61,"line":389},7,[59,391,392],{"class":374},"      'http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost'",[59,394,395],{"class":345},", ",[59,397,398],{"class":351},"\u002F\u002F for local dev\n",[59,400,402],{"class":61,"line":401},8,[59,403,404],{"class":345},"    ];\n",[59,406,408],{"class":61,"line":407},9,[59,409,411],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":410},true,"\n",[59,413,415,417,420,422,425,428,431,434,437,440,443],{"class":61,"line":414},10,[59,416,358],{"class":322},[59,418,419],{"class":361}," referer",[59,421,365],{"class":322},[59,423,424],{"class":345}," request.headers.",[59,426,427],{"class":338},"get",[59,429,430],{"class":345},"(",[59,432,433],{"class":374},"'Referer'",